previous: Computer scientist Dr. Raphael Finkel maintains a hub of Yiddish-language resources, including a searchable dictionary[92] and spell checker.[93]

Many websites on the Internet are in Yiddish. In January 2013, The Yiddish Forward announced the launch of the new daily version of their newspaper's website, which has been active since 1999 as an online weekly, supplied with radio and video programs, a literary section for fiction writers and a special blog written in local contemporary Hasidic dialects.[91]
